narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Understanding of type and graphic design

How to approach design with clarity, purpose, and ambition. This class seriously changes the way you look at form and content and how details and compositions work together to create a particular effect. You learn how to question design while learning how to grow as a designer.
InDesign, understanding how to visualize ideas through Typography, and convey ideas via Typography.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Weaknesses: Maybe a tutorial for printer issues is necessary lol
Strengths: Pin ups, class engagement, vibe, TA, teacher

Strengths: Prof is incredible, we love Alice!!! She is so understanding, supportive, welcoming, and just brilliant. It is a small seminar class where you will look at each other's work so you end up becoming really close with others in the class which I find as really rewarding. The assignments are all really interesting and rigorous in a way that exposes you to the principles of design while allowing room for your own experimentation. Weakness: The 8:30 am schedule was a quite hard not going to lie, but I will say if there is any class at Yale worth waking up for on a Friday, it is Typography!
I really enjoyed the course structure of multiple revising phases, which helped me develop more thorough and conveniencing works.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! I thought that this class was extremely engaging and was really designed to help me understand typography and how to integrate typography into my design.

Yes. I would recommend this to anyone interested in design with or without any background in it. It is a class that continues off of the intro graphic design class and is just incredibly rewarding and fun overall. The assignments are really engaging and the work is honestly a fun outlet/break from other classes.
Yes, it helped with my other studio courses about visualizations and thinking through visual design.
